  "text": "Lower PMHBR scores correspond to higher likelihoods for the mutation to be presented across the population. As remarked in Marty et al. [CITATION_1] , the properties of the harmonic average imply that the lowest BRi has the biggest impact on the value of PMHBR (although all 6 terms in the summation can contribute). Because of this and the fact that HLA-C proteins are generally expressed at lower levels with respect to HLA-A and HLA-B 50 , in the supplementary materials we also report analyses in which the two HLA-C allotypes are omitted from the calculation of the harmonic average in (1).",
